quran[75]{c,v,t}:
  87,1,"Glorify the name of your Master, the highest"
  87,2,"The One who created, then shaped"
  87,3,and the One who decreed and guided
  87,4,and the One who brought out the pastures
  87,5,then He made it dried up and black
  87,6,"We are going to read (Quran) to you, and you will not forget"
  87,7,except what God wants. Indeed He knows the evident and what is hidden
  87,8,And We make you ready for the easier way
  87,9,So remind if the reminder benefits
  87,10,"Then anyone who fears, is going to take notice"
  87,11,while the most miserable ones avoid it
  87,12,the one who enters (and burns in) the great fire
  87,13,he does not die and he does not live in there
  87,14,Everyone has succeeded who purified (himself)
  87,15,"and remembered the name of his Master, and prayed"
  87,16,"No, but you prefer this world's life"
  87,17,while the hereafter is better and more lasting
  87,18,Indeed this is in the earlier scriptures
  87,19,scriptures of Abraham and Moses
  88,1,Did the story of the overwhelming come to you
  88,2,On that day (some) faces are humble
  88,3,"working hard, exhausted"
  88,4,entering (and burning in) a scorching fire
  88,5,they are made to drink from a boiling spring
  88,6,There is no food for them except from a thorny plant
  88,7,that does not nourish and it does not satisfy hunger
  88,8,On that day (other) faces are delightful
  88,9,pleased with their effort
  88,10,in an excellent garden
  88,11,they do not hear any useless talk in it
  88,12,a running spring in it
  88,13,raised sofas in it
  88,14,and drinking glasses set in place
  88,15,and pillows arranged in rows
  88,16,and spread out rugs
  88,17,"Do they not look at the camel, how it is created"
  88,18,"And at the sky, how it is raised"
  88,19,"And at the mountain, how it is set up"
  88,20,"And at the earth, how it is spread out"
  88,21,"So remind (them), for you are only to remind"
  88,22,You are not an overseer for them
  88,23,But anyone who turns away and disbelieves
  88,24,then God punishes him with the great punishment
  88,25,Indeed their return is to Us
  88,26,then indeed their accounting is on Us
  89,1,By the dawn
  89,2,and by the ten nights
  89,3,and by the even and the odd
  89,4,and by the night when it goes away
  89,5,Is there an oath in that for one who has understanding
  89,6,Did you not see what your Master did with Aad
  89,7,(people of) Iram (a city) with the pillars
  89,8,the like of which was not created in the lands
  89,9,and Thamud those who carved out the rocks in the valley
  89,10,and Pharaoh having the stakes (pyramids)
  89,11,Those who rebelled in the lands
  89,12,and increased the corruption in it
  89,13,so your Master unleashed the whip of punishment on them
  89,14,Indeed your Master is on the watch
  89,15,"As for the human being, when his Master tests him and honors him and favors him, then he says: my Master honored me"
  89,16,"But when his Master tests him and decreases his provisions for him, then he says: my Master dishonored me"
  89,17,"No way, but you do not respect the orphan"
  89,18,and you do not encourage one another about feeding the poor
  89,19,"and you eat up the inheritance, eating up altogether"
  89,20,"and you love the wealth, a great deal of love"
  89,21,"No way, when the earth is pounded, crushed and leveled"
  89,22,"and you Master comes, and the angels (come) row by row"
  89,23,"and on that day hell is brought, on that day the human being takes notice, but what (use) does the notice have for him"
  89,24,"He says: I wish that I had sent ahead (something) for my (new) life"
  89,25,So on that day no one punishes as He punishes
  89,26,and no one ties up as He ties up
  89,27,You the reassured soul
  89,28,"return to your Master, pleased (with Him) and pleasing (to Him)"
  89,29,so you enter among My servants
  89,30,and you enter My garden